
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Learning to Design Organizations and Learning from Designing Them
AU  - Dunbar, Roger L. M.
AU  - Starbuck, William H.
Y1  - 2006/04/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/orsc.1060.0181
DO  - 10.1287/orsc.1060.0181
T2  - Organization Science
JF  - Organization Science
JO  - Organization Science
SP  - 171
EP  - 178
VL  - 17
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The academic focus of organization studies has unfortunately drifted over the years from the issues that organizations pose for their members and their societies, and the issues that confront people who seek to improve organizations. However, studies of efforts to design organizations can help us to better understand organizations and may also help us to improve them. The papers in this special issue of Organization Science describe several specific efforts to design organizations, telling why people wanted to make changes and what happened when people sought to make them.
