TY  - JOUR
T1  - Emergent by Design: Performance and Transformation at Infosys Technologies
AU  - Garud, Raghu
AU  - Kumaraswamy, Arun
AU  - Sambamurthy, V.
Y1  - 2006/04/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/orsc.1050.0179
DO  - 10.1287/orsc.1050.0179
T2  - Organization Science
JF  - Organization Science
JO  - Organization Science
SP  - 277
EP  - 286
VL  - 17
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We explore how organizations may be designed to transform themselves even as they continue to perform seamlessly on a day-to-day basis. Our inquiry frame recognizes that organizational designs comprise several elements?people, technologies, processes, and governance. Our study of an exemplary organization, Infosys Technologies, yields two insights. At Infosys, each design element is seeded with generative properties. As these design elements interact, reinforcing and balancing one another, an overall organizational platform of resources, capabilities, and options emerges. The company draws on this emergent platform to perform in real time even as it transforms itself to adapt to changing environments.
AB  - We explore how organizations may be designed to transform themselves even as they continue to perform seamlessly on a day-to-day basis. Our inquiry frame recognizes that organizational designs comprise several elements?people, technologies, processes, and governance. Our study of an exemplary organization, Infosys Technologies, yields two insights. At Infosys, each design element is seeded with generative properties. As these design elements interact, reinforcing and balancing one another, an overall organizational platform of resources, capabilities, and options emerges. The company draws on this emergent platform to perform in real time even as it transforms itself to adapt to changing environments.
